classes
a public github repository within the organization uafseismo
Repository for two classes at University of Alaska Fairbanks by Carl Tape:
   seismo  : GEOS 626 Applied Seismology
   inverse : GEOS 627 Inverse Problems and Parameter Estimation
contact: Carl Tape (ctape@alaska.edu)

Course webpages:
GEOS 626: http://www.giseis.alaska.edu/input/carl/teaching/seis/aseis.html  
GEOS 627: http://www.giseis.alaska.edu/input/carl/teaching/inverse/inv.html 

The repository can be obtained form github with this command:
git clone https://github.com/uafseismo/classes.git

Dependencies:

inverse
+ Matlab
+ Several examples require the matlab toolbox that comes with the textbook by Aster, Borchers, and Thurber, Parameter Estimation and Inverse Problems.

seismo
+ Matlab
+ Several examples require access to waveform databases that are only visible at UAF.
+ Several examples require the Matlab Waveform Toolbox:
  https://github.com/geoscience-community-codes/GISMO  
+ Some exercises require utilities within the private github repository
  https://github.com/uafseismo/GEOTOOLS  
  UAF students can obtain this repository via instructions from class.
+ Some scripts in GEOTOOLS require the public repository compearth
  https://github.com/carltape/compearth  

====
